The paper discusses the integration of AI into wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for new technologies and protocols to support AI-enabled wireless networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of AI in multimedia applications, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
